cs.DC, cs.CE, cs.Distributed, cs.SY, cs.NI 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper discusses the execution of Bag-of-Distributed-Tasks (BoDT) on the Cloud, which involves distributed computing. 
2. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper discusses the use of Cloud computing to execute BoDT applications, which can be used in various computational engineering and science fields. 
3. cs.Distributed (Distributed Computing) - The paper discusses the execution of distributed tasks on the Cloud, which falls under the category of distributed computing. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a heuristic algorithm to find an execution plan that takes budget constraints into account, which can be applied in systems and control. 
5. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the use of Cloud computing, which involves networking and internet architecture.
